
[1]terrify

   TER'RIFY, v.t. [L. terror and facio, to make.]

   To frighten; to alarm or shock with fear.

   They were terrified and affrighted. Luke 24.

   When ye shall hear of wars and commotions, be not terrified. Luke 21.
   Job.7.
